<example name="stitch together">
<inflection aspect="ns" form="full" person="ns" tense="past" voice="active"/>
<text>
    It isn't every day that we hear a Violetta who can sing the first
    act's high-flying music with all the little notes perfectly
    pitched and neatly stitched *trace* together. 
</text>
        <arg f="MNR" n="M">neatly</arg>
        <rel>stitched</rel>
        <arg n="1">*trace* -&gt;  all the little notes</arg>
        <arg n="3">together</arg>
</example>

<note>
The 'together' is redundant but still argument-y.
</note>

<example name="ouch" src="pin.01">
  <text>
